Class State<S,A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.builtin.State<S,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the state type
    A - the result type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Applicative<A,State<S,?>>, com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functor.Functor<A,State<S,?>>, com.jnape.palatable.lambda.monad.Monad<A,State<S,?>>

    public final class State<S,A>
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.jnape.palatable.lambda.monad.Monad<A,State<S,?>>
    The state Monad, useful for iteratively building up state and state-contextualized result.

    For more information, read about the state monad.
